runs.comm: turned to leg to loud cheers
half forward, a thick inside edge squirts into the leg side
wide and full, driven hard into the ground and back to the bowler
super ball, beats the outside edge and he plays a rather nothing shot with a slightly open face
one step and heaved through midwicket, there is a man in the deep but he's too square to cut that off
pulled for four past the man just behind square on the edge of the circle
a step down the track and to off, misses and a loud appeal as it hits him on the pads but well outside off
a big stride to leg, the ball is outside off and he ends up groping tennis-like and misses
leaves him off the seam, just short and with the batsman anchored to the crease outside leg stump, he can't really play any more than a airy waft
think inside edge into the on side
jags back from short of a length and Wright cramped as he looks to work into the off side, it takes him on the gloves and McCullum does really well to dive to his right as the ball dies on him
shimmies to the off and helps the ball behind square on the leg side ...fine leg is up in the circle and has no chance
dropped ... slashed high to third man off a thick outside edge.Chris Martin is slow to start and so has to dive forward and can't hold on
driven over long-on for six, flat and hard and four rows back but never more than eight feet off the ground
bottom-handed slog to deep midwicket
turned to deep midwicket, Pietersen again moves to the off to give himself freedom to work the leg side
full toss patted to Ross Taylor at midwicket, a quick single but no more
overpitched, a sweet straight drive to the right of the bowler, all along the ground and it scurries away unhindered with nobody out in the deep

short, pulled straight to deep midwicket, the rather large Jesse Ryder did not have to move which is probably just as well. The ball came off the toe-end of the bat which is why it didn't carry the boundary
driven on the up through the covers between the two men in the ring. He really thumped that ...
firm drive past the bowler but mid-off covers
tip and run into the off side
wide but slashed hard to cover who stops well
driven between cover and point, not quite timed and Taylor makes a sliding stop and return ten yards in from the boundary
turned to wide midwicket
driven hard back at Oram who gets down well for a big man, quickly enough to force Pietersen, backing up, to dive for safety in case there's a shy at the stumps
slashed through where second slip would have been had he not just been moved
checked push to point and a loud yell of "no" from bell even as he looks to set off for the single
straight drive squirts off a thick edge to deep midwicket
worked to short fine leg
slower ball, a thick edge and it goes fine enough to beat the man back on the boundary
slashing drive, a thick inside edge and the ball squeezes past leg stump and too wide for McCullum to have any chance, four runs to fine leg
short, pulled and Patel looks to be beaten at deep midwicket but slides and pulls the ball back brilliantly
he dances down the pitch but can't get any power in the shot and it goes to mid-off
full toss -  Pietersen started to come and then went back - driven hard between mid-off and extra cover, super timing
wide, slashed to cover
slightly short, pushed to cover
slower ball, chipped over mid-on who can't scurry back and the ball drops two or three yards over him
pushed to long-on
short and wide, Bell slaps that hard over point and away
corker yorker does for Bell, he was looking to make room to hit to the off and was completely cleaned up
edged past backward point
short and pulled off the front foot for six over long-on, absolutely hammered
slower ball, Pietersen pushed defensively into the off side
full toss, he gets slightly inside out as he drives to longish-off
slightly slower outside off, Collingwood beaten as he looks to push into the covers
wide, Collingwood walks to the off to play it and misses, there was a noise but the appeal was no more than half hearted
punched off the back foot into the covers
driven on the trot to mid-off
worked to midwicket, he realised there was no big shot to be played and settled for the single
yorker length, squirted to backward point
turned to deepish square, there never looked to be a second there but they ran really quickly
turned to square leg

Collingwood steps to the off and tries to sweep, the length is Ok for that but he gets in a muddle and ends up dumped on the ground with the ball at his feet. No runs and not much remaining dignity either ...
full toss driven to long-on
full, driven to extra cover, well bowled, that's the spot
heaved with his head in the air, it falls five yards inside the rope at deep midwicket and plugs, the fielder seems to stop it just in time but his feet clipped the boundary marker
turned into the on side
he dances down the track and hammers low to midwicket where Ross Taylor dives to his right and holds the ball a foot above the turf
driven into the off side
good start and a big cheer, full and turned to midwicket who slides on his knees to stop
straight drive, long-on round to field but he cannot prevent the second
really sharp yorker which Shah does well to keep out
wristy flick through midwicket, classic Shah stroke
steered with an open face to backward point
again backward point into action but this time they take on his arm and win
driven from the crease to long-on
pushed gently to long-on for an ambled single
worked round the corner with the spin
patted to long-on
pushed to extra cover
effortless flick to the right of long-on, never a chance and it falls a yard inside the rope
up in the blockhole, dug out to midwicket
driven with an open face behind square on the off side
slower ball, he waits and then heaves it into the leg side
lovely shot, Shah flicks the ball over midwicket, using his feet to get to it, six all the way
the bowler overcorrects but Shah is expecting it and drives straight and hard, long-off has no chance
prodded into the off side, Shah was looking for the second - which was never on - but Collingwood sent him back
good start, Shah defends
Shah sweeps across the line, misses, it's straight and that's a simple decision for the umpire
full and driven to extra cover
outside off, a slash and a miss
driven into the off side
full toss clipped through midwicket for the single
firm drive to deep cover
angled in at his feet, he falls over as he plays it
down the leg and that's the first wide of the day
he looks to run it to third man but it's far too close to him and the ball squeezes over the top of off stump
tight over this one, pushed to mid-off
pushed to deep cover, placed and not hit hard
paddled from some way outside off stump, up in the air and two yards short of backward square leg, and then there's a chance of a run-out at the bowler's end but the throw is wide
squirted into the on side
thumped to long-on
driven high over long-on, he middled that and some, and it carries into the second tier of the stand
and more of the same, and that went even further if anything
this is The Oval revisited ... another swing high over long-on, many rows back
Patel switches to round the wicket but it makes not a scrap of difference ... another big swing of the arms and a fourth six disappears over long-on
full toss swished behind square, effortless and effective
thick inside edge to deep backward square leg
short, pulled hard to deep midwicket where Ryder flings himself full stretch to his right, gets a hand to it but can't hold on
he steps to leg and cuts the ball to third man where Patel hardly had to move
slower, he waits and paddles into the leg side
pushed to cover, tip and run and a slight misfield ensures there are no alarms
full toss punched to long-on, he stepped to the off to hit it and Southee did well to follow him and restrict his options
rather airy drive, leaning back, to Styris at extra cover ... he takes it above his head, spills it, grabs at it with his right hand, juggles again and finally takes it at the third time of asking
thick inside edge goes past his leg stump and runs to fine leg for four
full outside off, Swann gives himself too much room and misses
very hard drive, Styris at extra cover makes a good tumbling stop five yards outside the circle
waist-high full toss, Broad misses out and his pull dribbles out to square leg
full toss driven straight and the two men in the deep cannot get round as it thuds into the sightscreen
slower ball, flicked to deep midwicket
good yorker, well played by Swann as he squirts it into the off side
slower ball, Broad gets under it, plenty of elevation but no distance. Styris at midwicket watches it like a hawk and makes no mistake
dropped ... thumped to midwicket, an inch off the ground by the time it reaches the diving fielder. That would have been an amazing catch ...
slower ball, beats the bat and McCullum applauds enthusiastically
good length and a hint of inswing, Swann can do no more than work the ball to long-on
full and wide, too good for a swishing Sidebottom
wide again but a thick edge with a hint of an open face, too fine for third man to have a chance
leans back and slogs, the ball falls into space in the covers
wide and full, two feet off a yorker, Swann leans back and places the ball between fielders behind square on the off

driven to long-off, it should have been one but Sidebottom was coming back come what may ... th throw was not great and there could have been an overthrow had Sidebottom not been going so fast to make his ground at the non-striker's end
